text: Park County is a county in the U.S. state of Wyoming. It was created on February 15, 1909. As of 2020, 29,624 people lived there. Park County's seat is Cody. ==Communities== === Cities === *Cody (county seat) *Powell === Towns === *Frannie *Meeteetse === Census-designated places === *Garland *Ralston *Mammoth ===Unincorporated communities=== *Clark *Wapiti *Yanceys ==References== ==Other websites== *Official county website Category:1911 establishments in Wyoming
